<div class="teidiv0" id="index.xml-body.1_div.4">
<h2><span class="headingNumber">4. </span><span class="head"> EXPENDITURES. </span></h2>
<p>----</p>
<p>SUPPORT OF SCHOOLS.</p>
<p>The money for the support of Schools has been apportioned among the several<br />
                    Districts according to the basis established by the town in 1849, and the<br />
                    following table exhibits the amount belonging to each: </p>
<div class="p">
<ul><li class="item">Appropriation for 1856-7, $2800 00</li>
<li class="item">" " High School and deficiency in Centre District, 700 00</li>
<li class="item">Income Beaton and Cummings Donations, 95 94</li>
<li class="item">" State School Fund, 89 31</li>
<li class="item">Payment by Town of Lincoln to District No. 2, 8 72</li>
<li class="item">-----$3693 97</li>
</ul></div>
<p>TABLE OF DIVISION.</p>
<div class="p">
<ul><li class="item">Dist. No. 1--51 per cent. and $700.00, $2222 48</li>
<li class="item">" No. 2--8 7-12 " and $8.72, 264 95</li>
<li class="item">" No. 3--7 3-4 " 231 35</li>
<li class="item">" No. 4--10 2-12 " 303 50</li>
<li class="item">" No. 5--8 1-4 " 246 29</li>
<li class="item"> " No. 6--7 1-8 " 212 70</li>
<li class="item">" No. 7--7 1-8 " 212 70</li>
<li class="item">---$3693 97</li>
</ul></div>
<p>----</p>
<p>ACCOUNT WITH THE SEVERAL DISTRICTS.</p>
<div class="p">
                    <span class="listhead"><em>District No.</em> 1.</span>
<ul><li class="item">Balance in Treasury, March, 1856, $492 13</li>
<li class="item">Appropriation, "380026"c., 2222 48</li>
<li class="item">---$2714 61</li>
<li class="item">Paid Henry Chase. for teaching High School, $545 45</li>
<li class="item">Sarah C. Buttrick, " Intermediate, 150 00</li>
